						<summary>

						<p>Fragmentary slab built into the wall of the agasi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Jagadēkamalla [Jayasiṁha II] 1033 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This very much damaged record belongs to the reign of Chālukya Jagadēkamalla who was ruling the empire from the capital [Ēta]giri. Probably it recorded grant of 15 <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> land to some one [name lost] and 12 mattar land to a Bhaṭara [name lost]. Perhaps these grants are to a god and to its <hi rend="italic">sthānapati</hi> respectively.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 955, Śrīmukha, Chaitra, Amāvāsye, Sunday, <hi rend="italic">sankrānti.</hi> Probably it corresponds to 1033 A.D., April 2 f.d.t. 25, Monday. </p>						

						</summary>
